        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all Gilead; Mount Gilead, and the cities belonging to it, a very fruitful country, half of which fell to the share of the Reubenites, and the rest to the half tribe of Manasseh: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all Bashan; of which Og was king, called Batanea, a very fertile country, as before observed: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "unto Salcah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan; which seem to be frontier cities of the latter: see Deuteronomy 1:4. The former, Adrichomius (p) says, was situated by the city Geshur and Mount Hermon, and was the boundary of the country of Bashan to the north; and according to Benjamin of Tudela (q), it was half a day's journey from Gilead: as Edrei seems to be its boundary to the south. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "unto Salcah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan; which seem to be frontier cities of the latter: see ",
            "children": []
